{
  "page": "Lord Stackspear (father of Alys)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> The canonicity of the character presented in this article is currently unclear. They are not mentioned in the published works of <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>. However, they are mentioned in an expanded version of the Westerlands chapter from <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The World of Ice and Fire\">The World of Ice and Fire</a></i> that was published on Martin's website a few months before the book release date.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Until further information comes out, they should be considered a semi-canon character.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Stackspear\" title=\"House Stackspear\"><img alt=\"House Stackspear.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fa/House_Stackspear.svg/50px-House_Stackspear.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fa/House_Stackspear.svg/75px-House_Stackspear.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fa/House_Stackspear.svg/100px-House_Stackspear.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Lord Stackspear</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Stackspear\" title=\"House Stackspear\"><img alt=\"House Stackspear.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fa/House_Stackspear.svg/50px-House_Stackspear.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fa/House_Stackspear.svg/75px-House_Stackspear.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fa/House_Stackspear.svg/100px-House_Stackspear.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">Lord</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Stackspear\" title=\"House Stackspear\">House Stackspear</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">Westermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Alys_Stackspear\" title=\"Alys Stackspear\">Alys Stackspear</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Lord Stackspear</b> was the head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stackspear\" title=\"House Stackspear\">House Stackspear</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon V Targaryen</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Stackspear_(father_of_Alys)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord Stackspear's daughter, <a href=\"/index.php/Alys_Stackspear\" title=\"Alys Stackspear\">Alys Stackspear</a>, was hastly married to the fifteen-year-old <a href=\"/index.php/Jason_Lannister_(son_of_Gerold)\" title=\"Jason Lannister (son of Gerold)\">Jason Lannister</a> after he took her maidenhood and got her pregnant. The marriage was short lived as Alys died giving birth to their son, <a href=\"/index.php/Damon_Lannister_(son_of_Jason)\" title=\"Damon Lannister (son of Jason)\">Damon Lannister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the misrule of the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a> by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">Tytos Lannister</a>, Lord Stackspear doubled the taxes on his <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a>. Ignoring his liege lord's protests, he hired a company of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantene</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellswords</a> to enforce his extortion.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord Stackspear and his levies were later part of the host of Lord Tytos's son, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>, when he suppressed the <a href=\"/index.php/Reyne-Tarbeck_revolt\" title=\"Reyne-Tarbeck revolt\">Reyne-Tarbeck revolt</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/261_AC\" title=\"261 AC\">261&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Stackspear_(father_of_Alys)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord Stackspear had one daughter, <a href=\"/index.php/Alys_Stackspear\" title=\"Alys Stackspear\">Alys Stackspear</a>. His relation to the current head of House Stackspear, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Selmond_Stackspear\" title=\"Selmond Stackspear\">Selmond</a>, is unknown. He may have been Selmond's grandfather.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Stackspear_(father_of_Alys)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-sample-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-sample_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-sample_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-sample_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-sample_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>: The Westerlands (unabridged). georgerrmartin.com: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.georgerrmartin.com/world-of-ice-and-fire-sample/\">WORLD OF ICE AND FIRE SAMPLE</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404212041\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.064 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.243 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 413/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 2402/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 6901/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1115/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 6/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion dep